This is a simple implementation of a Naive Bayes classifier. The data that has been used is from http://openclassroom.stanford.edu .  (A compressed folder _is_ a part of the repo)
The implementation details can be  found at : 
http://rohitdholakia.com/blog/machine-learning/writing-your-own-naive-bayes-classifier/

Please feel free to leave comments at rohit@rohitdholakia.com
For building the dictionary , use :
Dictionary.py 
For training ,use :
Training.py  
For actual classification , use :
spamNonspam.py 

The arguments to be passed are specified in the code